--------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

--- Key Bindings / Linux Tricks ---

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

======================================================================
------------------------------------------------------------------
# CURSOR MOVEMENT
======================================================================
Key     |   Action
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-a  | Move cursor to beginning of the line
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-e  | Move cursor to the end of the line
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-f  | Move cursor forward one character == right arrow key
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-b  | Move cursor back one character == left arrow key
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Alt-f   | Move cursor forward one word
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Alt-b   | Move cursor backward one word
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-l  | Clear screen
======================================================================


======================================================================
------------------------------------------------------------------
# MODIFYING TEXT
=====================================================================
Key     |   Action
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-d  | Delete the character at the cursor location
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-t  | Transpose char at cursor location with preceding char
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Alt-t   | Transpose word at cursor location with preceding word
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Alt-l   | Convert from cursor -> EOL to lowercase
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Alt-u   | Convert from cursor -> EOL to UPPERCASE
======================================================================


======================================================================
------------------------------------------------------------------
# KILLING AND YANKING
======================================================================
Key     |   Action
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-k  | Kill text from cursor location to end-of-line
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-u  | Kill text from cursor to beginning-of-line
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Alt-d   | Kill text from cursor to end-of-word
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Alt+<-- | Kill text from cursor to beginning-of-word
--------|------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl-y  | Yank text from kill-ring and insert at cursor location
======================================================================


======================================================================
------------------------------------------------------------------
# SEARCHING HISTORY
----------------------

======================================================================

-> history | less				- pages history results
-> history | grep /usr/bin		- returns all commands matching pattern
-> !index						- history expansion operator to call command

-> script						- use this program to record/log complete session

